nano /etc/sudoers :to add superuser
su ibulak :to switch
groups ibulak
sudo usermod -aG docker ibulak :
    to add the user <your_nickname> to the docker group.
    usermod is a command that modifies a user's account.
    The -a flag tells usermod to append the user to the
    specified group (in this case, the docker group)
    The -G flag specifies the group to which the user should be added.